                    <li>
                        <span>WHY DO WE REQUIRE SOCIAL MEDIA GUIDELINES</span>
                        <p>In today&rsquo;s competitive world, the usage of media platforms (like Facebook, YouTube, WhatsApp, Snapchat, Instagram, Twitter, and LinkedIn) is rapidly increasing for all types of business promotions. The advantages and effectiveness of these platforms cannot be ignored but the negative usage of these platforms cannot be ignored also. That's why the requirement of a few guidelines is so necessary so that its ethical usage may be promoted.</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                In the direct selling business, LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) play a vital role in marketing and selling LIFEONE product(s) and promoting LIFEONE as a brand and as an ethical direct selling entity.
                            </li>
                            <li>In the outer world, the direct seller(s) are a direct representation of the LIFEONE. Any wrong communication regarding LIFEONE products and/or services, intentional or unintentional may cause a direct negative impact on the business of LIFEONE.</li>
                            <li>While promoting LIFEONE product(s) and services in Social Media Platform like Facebook, YouTube, WhatsApp etc; LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) can only use product(s) photographs, creatives, brochures, training material, business promotion tools, Logo, and Trademark provided by LIFEONE. Usage of any other item(s) for the purpose of business promotion requires prior written approval by LIFEONE management.</li>
                            <li>Considering the above-mentioned factors, LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) are advised to strictly follow the mentioned guidelines while promoting his/her LIFEONE business. Any violation of these guidelines shall be taken very seriously and strict actions may be taken against the defaulter.</li>
                            <li>LIFEONE disclaims any liability of any nature for any loss caused to anyone due to any independent act (which is against these Guidelines) of LIFEONE Direct Seller(s).</li>


                        </ol>

                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span>HOW TO PROMOTE LIFEONE PRODUCTS &amp; SERVICES IN MEDIA PLATFORMS</span>


                        <p>LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) shall strictly adhere to the following instructions while making any promotion of LIFEONE products and/or services in all Media Platforms-</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                All content used in media platforms must be 100% real, and truthful.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                There must be zero intentional or unintentional attempts of Mis-selling LIFEONE product(s) and services. Mis-selling means selling a product or service by misrepresenting in order to successfully complete a sale and includes providing consumers with misleading information about a product or service or omitting key information about a product or providing information that makes the product appear to be something it is not.
                            </li>
                            <li>No information and/or communication from LIFEONE Direct Seller on the media platforms shall neither distort facts nor mislead the consumer.</li>
                            <li>No information and/or communication neither digitally nor verbally in any media campaign shall be permitted to contain any claim, which is not substantiated or approved by LIFEONE management team.</li>
                            <li>Any media campaign must not contain any information which is not approved by LIFEONE and at the same time against the direct selling guidelines of the government of India.</li>





                            <li>
                                LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) shall not write and post texts covering LIFEONE product(s) and/or services. They are also not authorized to put creatives, or content visuals in media platforms, which cannot be substantiated or is not known fact.
<li>
                            <li>LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) shall not misrepresent the price, quality, packaging, usage, dosage, or performance of LIFEONE products, etc. LIFEONE Direct Seller(s) may use only those claims and information as available on LIFEONE Products and/or provided in the product information materials like product catalogues, training modules, etc. duly approved by LIFEONE.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <span>BE ETHICAL IN BUSINESS</span>
                        <p>Every direct seller of LifeoneWellness must follow and practice the right and ethical business rules. Every direct seller needs to ensure that all digital Information posted on media platforms must not contain that information that directly or indirectly affects adversely for any other direct selling company.</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Don&rsquo;t compare LifeoneWellness product(s) with the product(s) of any other direct-selling company.</li>
                            <li>
                                Don&rsquo;t post any derogatory remarks relating to the product(s) of any other direct-selling company in the form of text messages, voice messages, or in digital creatives.
                            </li>
                            <li>Don&rsquo;t mislead your customers with the wrong Information (like product price, design, indications, dosage, and usage) of the product(s) that belongs to another direct selling company.</li>
                            <li>Don&rsquo;t copy and post-digital creatives, slogans, presentations, or videos of any other direct- selling company using your media platforms.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <span>HOW TO REPRESENT YOURSELF ON SOCIAL MEDIA PLATFORMS</span>

                        <p>While you are working as an independent business owner/direct seller of LifeoneWellness, it is really very important to learn how you should present yourself on social media platforms. A simple mistake in representation may be a reason for huge business loss. So, every direct seller of LifeoneWellness must follow the following:</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>LifeoneWellness direct seller(s) should mention their name as well as their designation/rank in their social media profile. For example, instead of mentioning &lsquo;Works at LifeoneWellness&rsquo;, they should mention it like &lsquo;Emerald (or any other rank you have achieved) at LifeoneWellness&rsquo;.</li>
                            <li>
                                No LifeoneWellness direct seller is authorize to use LifeoneWellness Logo, and Trademarks in their social media profile of any social media platform.
                            </li>
                            <li>No LifeoneWellness direct seller(s) is authorize to create a page, chat group, profile page on social media platforms using the words like &lsquo;LifeoneWellness Management&rsquo;, &lsquo;Official LifeoneWellness&rsquo;, &lsquo;LifeoneWellness Official&rsquo;, and &lsquo;LifeoneWellness Company&rsquo;.</li>
                            <li>Every LifeoneWellness direct seller(s) must provide a brief information about their true business relationship with LifeoneWellness in their profile page of all social media platforms.</li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <span>WHAT YOU CAN&rsquo;T DO IN SOCIAL MEDIA PLATFORM</span>


                        <p>LifeoneWellness Direct Seller(s) must not develop any Software, App, and Website connecting LifeoneWellness mobile app and/or website or its business activities with such Software, App, and Website. LifeoneWellness never allows any LifeoneWellness Direct Seller(s) to develop any Software, Applications, and/or Website connecting LifeoneWellness or its business activities. Further, LifeoneWellness disclaims any</p>

                        <p>liability of any nature for any loss caused to anyone due to the development, or usage of such Software, Applications, and/or Website.</p>
                    </li>
